briefTitle: Phase 3 Extension Study of the Safety and Efficacy of Aldurazyme® (Laronidase) in Mucopolysaccharidosis I (MPS I) Patients
officialTitle: A Multicenter, Multinational, Open-Label Extension Study of the Safety and Efficacy of Aldurazyme® (Laronidase) in Patients With Mucopolysaccharidosis I
summary: This study is being conducted to collect additional long-term efficacy and safety data of Aldurazyme® (laronidase) patients with MPS I disease. Patients who were previously enrolled in the Phase 3 Double-Blind Study will be enrolled in this study.

primaryOutcome.measure: Change From Baseline to Week 182 in Percent Predicted Forced Vital Capacity (FVC)
